Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane found that the president deliberately misled Parliament about money received from Bosasa for his ANC presidential campaign. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa addressed the media on Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane's report on Sunday. Mkhwebane found Ramaphosa deliberately misled Parliament about money he received from Bosasa for his ANC presidential campaign. READ: Ramaphosa misled Parliament on Bosasa donation: Mkhwebane She says Parliament's Ethics Committee should decide on a sanction for the President. But, he's not an MP. READ: PP's findings: President maintains innocence Ramaphosa initially said the R500, 000 payment was made to his son for services rendered. He later retracted the answer and clarified that it was a donation to his ANC presidential campaign.